# Accessibility Guidelines

## Accessibility Philosophy

The Navigator portfolio aims for WCAG 2.1 AA compliance with elements of AAA. Every user, regardless of ability, should experience the full portfolio.

## Skip Link

The site includes a skip link for keyboard users:

```jsx
// In App.jsx - First focusable element
<a href="#main-content" className="skip-link">
  Skip to main content
</a>

// Main content target
<main id="main-content" role="main">
```

Skip link styles in `index.css`:
- Hidden by default (`top: -3rem`)
- Appears on focus (`top: 1rem`)
- High contrast gradient background

## Semantic HTML Structure

### Page Structure

```jsx
<div className="app-container">
  <a href="#main-content" className="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
  <nav role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">
    {/* Navigation */}
  </nav>
  
  <main id="main-content" role="main">
    <section id="hero" aria-label="Hero section">
    <section id="career" aria-labelledby="career-heading">
    <section id="projects" aria-labelledby="projects-heading">
    <section id="skills" aria-labelledby="skills-heading">
    <section id="about" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  </main>
  
  <footer role="contentinfo">
    {/* Footer */}
  </footer>
</div>
```

### Section Headings

Each section needs a proper heading hierarchy:

```jsx
<section id="projects" aria-labelledby="projects-heading">
  <h2 id="projects-heading" className="text-section">
    Featured Projects
  </h2>
  {/* Section content */}
</section>
```

## ARIA Attributes

### Required Patterns

```jsx
// Sections with visible headings
<section aria-labelledby="heading-id">
  <h2 id="heading-id">Section Title</h2>

// Sections without visible headings
<section aria-label="Hero section">

// Decorative elements (hide from screen readers)
<div aria-hidden="true">
  {/* Decorative content */}
</div>

// Interactive cards
<article
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  aria-label="View project details for Project Name"
>

// External links
<a
  href={url}
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
  aria-label="View live demo (opens in new tab)"
>

// Icon-only buttons
<button aria-label="Toggle theme">
  <SunIcon />
</button>

// Loading states
<div aria-live="polite" aria-busy={isLoading}>
```

### ARIA Roles Reference

| Element | Role |
|---------|------|
| `<nav>` | `navigation` |
| `<main>` | `main` |
| `<footer>` | `contentinfo` |
| Clickable `<article>` | `button` |
| Tab panels | `tabpanel` with `aria-labelledby` |

## Keyboard Navigation

### Interactive Elements Must Be Keyboard Accessible

```jsx
// Cards that act as buttons
<article
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={handleClick}
  onKeyDown={(e) => e.key === 'Enter' && handleClick()}
>

// Custom buttons need Enter handling (Space is automatic)
<div
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={handleAction}
  onKeyDown={(e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
      e.preventDefault()
      handleAction()
    }
  }}
>
```

### Focus Styles

Focus outlines are customized but visible:

```css
/* In index.css */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid rgb(var(--navigator));
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

**Note**: Cards intentionally remove focus outline (`outline: none`) as they have other visual indicators (borders, shadows).

## Reduced Motion

### Always Check User Preference

```jsx
import { useReducedMotion } from '../../hooks/useReducedMotion'

const Component = () => {
  const prefersReducedMotion = useReducedMotion()

  // Skip animations entirely
  if (prefersReducedMotion) return {}

  // Or adjust animation timing
  style={{ 
    transitionDelay: prefersReducedMotion ? '0ms' : '200ms'
  }}

  // Or remove animation classes
  className={`${!prefersReducedMotion ? 'animate-float' : ''}`}
}
```

### CSS Fallback

The CSS also respects reduced motion:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}
```

## Color Contrast

### Minimum Contrast Ratios

| Text Type | Ratio | Requirement |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| Body text | 4.5:1 | WCAG AA |
| Large text (18px+ bold) | 3:1 | WCAG AA |
| Interactive elements | 3:1 | WCAG AA |
| Ideal target | 7:1 | WCAG AAA |

### Using Theme Colors

The color system maintains contrast in both themes:

```jsx
// High contrast text
className="text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-50"  // Near black/white

// Secondary text (still meets 4.5:1)
className="text-ink-400 dark:text-ink-100"

// Links have sufficient contrast
className="text-[rgb(var(--horizon))]"  // Teal
```

## Screen Reader Considerations

### Announce Dynamic Content

```jsx
// For content that updates
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  {statusMessage}
</div>

// For important updates
<div aria-live="assertive">
  {errorMessage}
</div>
```

### Descriptive Link Text

```jsx
// ✅ Descriptive
<a href={url} aria-label="View live demo for Geolink API">
  <ExternalLink />
</a>

// ❌ Not descriptive
<a href={url}>Click here</a>
```

### Image Alternatives

For decorative images (used in this portfolio):

```jsx
<div aria-hidden="true">
  <img src="decorative.svg" alt="" />
</div>
```

## Testing Checklist

### Keyboard Testing
- [ ] All interactive elements reachable via Tab
- [ ] Focus visible on all focused elements
- [ ] Enter/Space activates buttons and cards
- [ ] Escape closes modals
- [ ] Skip link works and is visible on focus

### Screen Reader Testing
- [ ] Page structure announced correctly
- [ ] All images have appropriate alt text
- [ ] Links have descriptive labels
- [ ] Forms have associated labels
- [ ] Dynamic content announced

### Visual Testing
- [ ] Passes color contrast checker
- [ ] Readable at 200% zoom
- [ ] Animations respect reduced motion
- [ ] Focus indicators visible

